com.jacobschneider.engine.math

Class Quaternion

  • Object
    • Quaternion

  • public class Quaternion
extends Object
    Immutable class representing a quaternion. A unit quaternion is a fast and efficient way to represent an orientation in 3D space. There is a one to one mapping between a unit quaternion in a rotation matrix (orthoganol matrix) and you can do this mapping by calling toMatrix(). This class does not guarantee an object is a unit quaternion but you can turn any Quaternion into a unit quaternion using normalize(). See (@link http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Quaternion) for more information.
    Author:
    Jacob

      • fromCameraVectors

        public static Quaternion fromCameraVectors(Vector3 centerPos,
                                           Vector3 lookAtPos,
                                           Vector3 upDir)
        Creates an orientation Quaternion from the typical camera vectors. Assumes the y-axis is the direction the camera points in and the z-axis is up.
        Parameters:
        centerPos - Center position of the camera
        lookAtPos - Position of focus of the camera. Y axis of camera points in this direction
        upDir - Desired up (z axis) direction of the camera.
        Returns:
        The Quaternion that represents the cameras orientation in 3D space.
